===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|宀|口|t1=house|t2=mouth|ls=ic}}, echos in a place. The original form of {{och-l|響}}. It was borrowed to represent {{zh-l|*𠨍}} ({{zh-l|*嚮}}) later. The mouth does not represent an opening as in {{zh-l|*高}} and {{zh-l|*谷}}. Compare {{zh-l|*冋}}.

